<TITLE> Dhanmondi students form human chain for war crimes trials </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 29 (bdnews24.com) -- Students from private universities located in the city's Dhanmondi area formed a human chain Saturday to demand the trial of those accused of committing war crimes during the 1971 Liberation War. The students gathered at Road15, Dhanmondi, in the afternoon, and called for the immediate formation of a special tribunal to bring the alleged war criminals to justice. They carried banners bearing the slogans: "It's time to stand firm against war criminals" and "War criminals must beg for mercy". bdnew
